    "Dana merged the museum into one for the arts as well, now called the Newark Museum in 1909, under the rubric of the Newark Museum Association, which he founded the same year.": [],
    "Dana's main interest was industrial art and design.": [],
    "He personally built many of the display cases from his home carpentry shop.": [],
    "Dana established contact with the director of the Folkwang Museum in Germany, <a href=\"/osthausk\">Karl Ernst Osthaus</a>.": [
